WEBVTT

00:09.680 --> 00:11.280
I don't think so, do you?

00:12.320 --> 00:14.800
It's only 29.99.

00:14.800 --> 00:16.320
Yeah, but where will you wear it?

00:16.320 --> 00:19.360
You never do anything except go
to school or study.

00:19.360 --> 00:22.880
Yeah. I've got library books that
have been out more than me.

00:22.880 --> 00:23.920
Exactly.

00:23.920 --> 00:25.200
I mean, why waste your money

00:25.200 --> 00:27.400
on something
that will never get worn, darling?

00:28.880 --> 00:30.640
OK, let's go.

00:30.640 --> 00:33.520
I have to pick up
your dad's athlete's foot powder.

00:33.520 --> 00:36.480
I'd hate to miss that,
but can I meet you at the car?

00:36.480 --> 00:37.720
All right, but don't be long.

00:37.720 --> 00:39.960
I've only got ten minutes left
on the parking.

00:53.640 --> 00:55.880
Excuse me, miss.

00:55.880 --> 00:57.320
I need to look in your bag.

00:57.320 --> 00:59.200
Why?

00:59.200 --> 01:01.280
Can I look in your bag, please?

01:08.320 --> 01:10.400
We've got a runner, boys.

01:12.920 --> 01:14.520
Sorry. Sorry!

01:17.480 --> 01:20.640
♪ Love is a burning thing

01:20.640 --> 01:24.640
♪ And it makes a fiery ring

01:25.600 --> 01:29.120
♪ Bound by wild desire

01:29.120 --> 01:32.720
♪ I fell into a ring of fire... ♪

01:32.720 --> 01:34.000
Stop!

01:34.000 --> 01:37.960
♪ I fell into a burning ring
of fire

01:37.960 --> 01:39.480
♪ I went down, down, down... ♪

01:39.480 --> 01:41.840
Sorry!
# And the flames went higher

01:41.840 --> 01:46.240
♪ And it burns, burns, burns,
the ring of fire

01:46.240 --> 01:52.280
♪ The ring of fire
The ring of fire... ♪

02:01.880 --> 02:03.200
Rani?

02:06.200 --> 02:07.800
What's going on?

02:51.480 --> 02:53.800
Do you remember what's special
about today, sweetie?

02:53.800 --> 02:55.600
Um, Grampa's coming to stay?

02:55.600 --> 02:56.840
That's right.

02:56.840 --> 03:00.680
Grandpa is funny and charming and
you're gonna like him very much.

03:00.680 --> 03:02.960
But I do need you to remember
one thing while he's here.

03:02.960 --> 03:06.680
I need you to remember that
Grandpa is a lying, thieving,

03:06.680 --> 03:08.360
selfish old bastard.

03:10.440 --> 03:12.880
Good luck. Cheers, mate.
Good luck, bro.

03:12.880 --> 03:14.520
And what is Grandpa?

03:15.440 --> 03:18.160
A lying, thieving,
selfish old bastard.

03:18.160 --> 03:20.440
Who can...?
Who can never be trusted.

03:20.440 --> 03:21.960
Good girl.

03:27.160 --> 03:28.800
Safe travels, Frank.

03:40.320 --> 03:45.160
Greetings and felicitations.
Margie, did you change your hair?

03:45.160 --> 03:46.240
Quite possibly, Frank,

03:46.240 --> 03:48.000
in the eight years
since I last saw you.

03:48.000 --> 03:49.880
This young buck must be Tom.

03:49.880 --> 03:51.680
Hey, dude, what's happening?

03:51.680 --> 03:55.640
Lord, oh, Lord,
who's this beautiful princess?

03:55.640 --> 03:57.040
Holly.

03:57.040 --> 03:58.920
Oh, what a pleasure.

03:58.920 --> 04:00.960
Where are we setting up, please?

04:00.960 --> 04:05.280
Between the hours of 7pm and 6am,
you will remain in this residence

04:05.280 --> 04:07.000
and the light will remain green.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.880
If you travel more than two metres
from this residence,

04:08.880 --> 04:10.360
the light turns red.

04:10.360 --> 04:11.440
Is that clear?

04:11.440 --> 04:13.520
Crystal. What happens
if it turns red?

04:13.520 --> 04:15.000
You get a little visit
from the police.

04:15.000 --> 04:16.240
Ooh.

04:17.360 --> 04:18.800
I'll show myself out.

04:18.800 --> 04:20.440
Thank you for your service.

04:21.600 --> 04:22.920
Why were you in prison?

04:22.920 --> 04:24.680
It was a misunderstanding.

04:24.680 --> 04:27.560
Grandpa misunderstood that you can't
forge signatures on cheques.

04:27.560 --> 04:29.920
Oooh... Ah!

04:31.000 --> 04:32.200
What's a cheque?

04:37.960 --> 04:41.680
All right, yep, yep. I do.

04:41.680 --> 04:44.440
Can I speak? Thank you.
I'm asking for two poxy weeks.

04:44.440 --> 04:45.480
No phones allowed. What?

04:45.480 --> 04:47.360
Back through the machine.
Empty your pockets.

04:47.360 --> 04:50.040
All right, Captain, slow down.
Just a middle-aged white man.

04:50.040 --> 04:53.040
All I'm carrying are keys
and unwanted back fat.

04:53.040 --> 04:54.280
No, listen, no.

04:54.280 --> 04:56.280
The Chinese deal is going through.
No phones allowed.

04:56.280 --> 04:57.920
What? No phones allowed.

04:57.920 --> 05:00.040
No phones allowed.
I have to call you back.

05:01.040 --> 05:02.680
And the bag. And the bag!

05:02.680 --> 05:07.320
Listen, I'm a businessman
from Bristol, not a jihadi bride.

05:09.360 --> 05:10.560
Are you wearing a belt?

05:10.560 --> 05:11.600
I am wearing a belt.

05:11.600 --> 05:14.040
Yes, I like it
when my trousers stay up. That OK?

05:15.280 --> 05:17.960
Thank you.
Where am I going please?

05:28.800 --> 05:32.040
Be careful, darling.
Just do whatever they tell you.

06:05.040 --> 06:06.480
This way.

06:24.760 --> 06:27.840
Hi there. I'm Greg.

06:27.840 --> 06:31.920
I'm 6'7" tall
and, no, it's not in proportion.

06:31.920 --> 06:34.400
If it was in proportion,
I'd be 8'3".

06:42.160 --> 06:45.280
Greetings and felicitations.
High pockets!

06:45.280 --> 06:47.040
What's tickin', chicken?

06:47.040 --> 06:50.160
Uh, it's finger-lickin', chicken.

06:50.160 --> 06:54.240
Good morning, ladies. Can I just
say? You're both looking beautiful.

06:54.240 --> 06:55.720
No, you can't.

06:55.720 --> 06:57.200
He can't tell you
that you're beautiful?

06:57.200 --> 06:59.440
We didn't ask him
for a verdict on our appearance.

06:59.440 --> 07:01.520
Sorry, but I say it like I find it.

07:01.520 --> 07:05.240
And, ladies, you're both
a right couple of swooners.

07:07.360 --> 07:10.720
Attention! Sit.

07:11.840 --> 07:13.520
Some people...

07:13.520 --> 07:17.240
..think that Community Payback
is an easy option.

07:17.240 --> 07:19.320
A soft touch.

07:19.320 --> 07:21.520
Newsflash -

07:21.520 --> 07:23.040
it ain't.

07:23.040 --> 07:27.040
You will repay your debt to society
by working the number of hours

07:27.040 --> 07:29.280
mandated by the court.

07:29.280 --> 07:32.480
My name is Diane Pemberley.
I'm your supervisor.

07:32.480 --> 07:37.160
And I can be a good guy...or
a mean bastard.

07:37.160 --> 07:38.680
Your choice.

07:38.680 --> 07:40.920
Good guy, please. You don't choose.

07:40.920 --> 07:42.840
You said it was our choice.
It was a figure of speech.

07:42.840 --> 07:45.200
It wasn't entirely clear.
Are you a trouble-maker?

07:45.200 --> 07:47.160
No, ma'am. Definitely not.

07:47.160 --> 07:50.440
When I call your name, say here.

07:50.440 --> 07:51.520
John Halloran.

07:51.520 --> 07:53.160
Here. Shouldn't be.

07:53.160 --> 07:54.280
Frank Sheldon?

07:54.280 --> 07:55.680
What's the agenda, Brenda?

07:55.680 --> 07:56.880
Christian Taylor.

07:56.880 --> 08:00.200
Yo. OK, what are you people not
getting? Just say here.

08:00.200 --> 08:01.560
Myrna Okeke.

08:01.560 --> 08:03.720
Here in body, not in spirit.

08:03.720 --> 08:06.680
I don't know what that means.
Gregory Dillard?

08:06.680 --> 08:07.880
Yeah, that's me.

08:07.880 --> 08:09.720
Can I just apologise
for the inappropriate joke

08:09.720 --> 08:12.000
earlier about things
being in proportion?

08:12.000 --> 08:16.160
To be honest, it's not even that
long. Although it is quite flat.

08:16.160 --> 08:17.400
Like a kipper.

08:17.400 --> 08:19.080
Just say here.

08:19.080 --> 08:20.400
Yeah, here. Yeah. Here.

08:20.400 --> 08:22.240
Rani Rekowski?

08:22.240 --> 08:24.160
Here. Thank you.

08:53.560 --> 08:59.280
You each have
over 100 hours to serve.

09:00.440 --> 09:01.800
You have been tasked

09:01.800 --> 09:05.400
with restoring this
into a community centre

09:05.400 --> 09:08.160
for the local...community.

09:09.160 --> 09:12.200
You will work four hours
each visit.

09:12.200 --> 09:16.160
Only when I am happy
with the work you have done

09:16.160 --> 09:18.760
will I log those four hours.

09:18.760 --> 09:20.080
Take another one.

09:20.080 --> 09:21.520
During clean-up duty,

09:21.520 --> 09:26.760
if you find a deceased animal
over 10k,

09:26.760 --> 09:28.960
do not touch it.

09:28.960 --> 09:31.600
That is the council's business.

09:31.600 --> 09:37.360
Anything under 10k -
vermin, cats, a small dog -

09:37.360 --> 09:38.960
that is yours.

09:38.960 --> 09:40.840
Can we keep it? No, you may not.

09:40.840 --> 09:43.520
Now, you may be wondering
about faeces.

09:43.520 --> 09:45.240
You read my mind.

09:45.240 --> 09:49.480
If you find human faeces,
do not touch it.

09:49.480 --> 09:53.400
You may handle
other species' faeces.

09:53.400 --> 09:54.760
Can we keep it?

09:54.760 --> 09:56.400
No, you may not.

09:56.400 --> 10:02.080
You are here for the next four
hours, people. You may begin!

10:14.600 --> 10:15.920
So, why're you here?

10:17.120 --> 10:20.000
Uh, oh, well, I'm here
because, uh,

10:20.000 --> 10:21.960
even though I run
a successful company

10:21.960 --> 10:24.240
making brake pads, pay my taxes,

10:24.240 --> 10:26.160
employ 52 people,

10:26.160 --> 10:29.560
we have a criminal justice system
that kowtows to the, uh,

10:29.560 --> 10:31.360
right-on leftie liberal brigade.

10:31.360 --> 10:33.960
I'm a right-on leftie liberal.
Are you sure?

10:33.960 --> 10:36.520
Seems like you can't really call
yourself a leftie these days

10:36.520 --> 10:39.200
unless you're a disabled
transgender vegan

10:39.200 --> 10:42.120
with a nut allergy
who makes their own soap.

10:42.120 --> 10:44.520
Are you reading that
straight off the Daily Mail website?

10:44.520 --> 10:46.120
Well, they're not wrong
about everything.

10:46.120 --> 10:48.080
I'm just saying, you watch yourself.

10:48.080 --> 10:50.840
Nothing the lefties like more
than eating their own.

10:50.840 --> 10:52.520
Unless they contain nuts.

10:58.280 --> 10:59.600
You're working too hard.

10:59.600 --> 11:02.120
You think it matters
if we clear this crap up or not?

11:02.120 --> 11:03.840
They just want to give us
something to do.

11:03.840 --> 11:07.120
I'd slow down if I were you.
You might burn yourself out.

11:08.640 --> 11:10.200
Also, you're making me look bad.

11:13.920 --> 11:16.440
What are you in for?

11:16.440 --> 11:18.120
I stole some stuff.

11:18.120 --> 11:20.640
Why would someone proper-smart
be stealing stuff?

11:20.640 --> 11:22.200
Who says I'm proper-smart?

11:22.200 --> 11:25.000
Well, I saw your bag
and it said Oxford University.

11:25.000 --> 11:28.960
My mum bought that when I went
to interview at Oxford University.

11:28.960 --> 11:30.600
Did you get in?

11:30.600 --> 11:33.600
Well, yeah,
but I'm not proper-smart.

11:33.600 --> 11:36.960
I just have parents who never bought
me a toy that wasn't educational.

11:36.960 --> 11:41.360
Oy, Miss Rekowski.
Less flirting, more exerting.

11:41.360 --> 11:43.960
No, I'm not flirting. I'm not.

11:43.960 --> 11:47.000
I wasn't flirting.
She weren't flirting. I was.

11:48.520 --> 11:49.560
Sorry.

11:55.120 --> 11:56.320
What's wrong?

12:12.400 --> 12:14.640
Hi, Gabby. Look this way.

12:14.640 --> 12:16.840
All right, Gabby?

12:16.840 --> 12:18.000
Hi, Gabby.

12:18.000 --> 12:19.360
Look at me, Gabby.

12:19.360 --> 12:20.640
Nice to see you again.

12:25.200 --> 12:28.200
Whoa! If I was 30 years younger...

12:28.200 --> 12:30.520
You'd still be twice her age.

12:30.520 --> 12:31.840
Thank you.

12:33.080 --> 12:35.240
Did you know? On Twitter,
everyone's been debating

12:35.240 --> 12:36.400
who you were gonna wear today.

12:36.400 --> 12:38.600
Today is about me learning
from my mistakes,

12:38.600 --> 12:40.480
and people are worrying
about what I'm wearing?

12:40.480 --> 12:41.600
That is sick.

12:41.600 --> 12:42.840
Who are you wearing?

12:42.840 --> 12:44.800
It's a Stella McCartney.
The Vampire's Wife.

12:44.800 --> 12:46.440
And shoes are Isabel Marant.

12:46.440 --> 12:47.520
Lovely.

12:47.520 --> 12:48.960
Am I supposed to know who she is?

12:48.960 --> 12:50.920
That's Lady Gabriella Penrose-Howe.

12:50.920 --> 12:53.080
She was on that reality show
where posh people have to give up

12:53.080 --> 12:54.680
their mobile phones
and their assistants.

12:54.680 --> 12:56.080
It was called No Service.

12:56.080 --> 12:57.360
I don't own a TV.

12:57.360 --> 12:59.120
Too busy making vegan soap?

12:59.120 --> 13:01.960
No. Too busy reading books.
You should try it.

13:01.960 --> 13:05.120
I read books. Yeah?
Any that aren't about the SAS?

13:05.120 --> 13:08.400
Hi. Hi, friends. I'm Gabby. Hi.

13:08.400 --> 13:10.520
Hi! Hi, I'm Lady Gabby.

13:10.520 --> 13:12.960
My preferred pronouns
are she, her and herself.

13:12.960 --> 13:15.600
I'm John. Bloke.

13:15.600 --> 13:16.920
I'm so sorry I'm late.

13:16.920 --> 13:18.480
I'm in charge here!

13:19.480 --> 13:22.320
Seriously?
Sorry, that came out wrong.

13:22.320 --> 13:23.800
Yeah, it did come out wrong. Gabby!

13:23.800 --> 13:25.200
They can't be here. Look this way.

13:25.200 --> 13:30.120
You can't be here! Go! Go!
Private property! Back! Scram!

13:31.760 --> 13:33.200
What are you wearing?

13:33.200 --> 13:34.880
Oh, it's Stella McCartney.

13:34.880 --> 13:36.920
This is a Vampire's Wife
and shoes are Isabel Marant.

13:36.920 --> 13:39.720
Thanks for asking. No, I don't mean,
"Ooh, what are you wearing?"

13:39.720 --> 13:41.640
cos I'm interested, I mean,
"What are you wearing?!"

13:41.640 --> 13:42.840
That is not appropriate.

13:42.840 --> 13:44.480
Put this on.

13:46.720 --> 13:49.200
Do I have to?
Yeah, it's not a fashion show.

13:49.200 --> 13:50.800
You're here
because you committed a crime.

13:50.800 --> 13:52.520
The person who designed this
committed the crime.

13:52.520 --> 13:55.560
I mean, someone call
the fashion police. Am I right?

13:55.560 --> 13:57.880
No, you're not right,
Michael McIntyre.

13:57.880 --> 13:59.920
I'm docking you two hours
for being late.

13:59.920 --> 14:01.720
Do you want another two
for being a smart-aleck?

14:01.720 --> 14:04.040
No. Right answer.

14:04.040 --> 14:05.680
Toilet breaks at my discretion.

14:05.680 --> 14:06.920
Any questions?

14:06.920 --> 14:08.360
Yeah, what is this?

14:08.360 --> 14:09.720
Hoe.

14:09.720 --> 14:10.920
Excuse me?

14:14.160 --> 14:17.200
Yo. Respect.

14:17.200 --> 14:18.840
What is that?

14:18.840 --> 14:21.800
It's a...it's a gang sign.
You're not...?

14:21.800 --> 14:25.480
No, it's Mr Spock's Vulcan salute
from Star Trek.

14:25.480 --> 14:27.800
I don't think so.

14:27.800 --> 14:28.920
Yeah, it is.

14:31.880 --> 14:34.200
Oh, yeah, that...
What am I thinking of, then?

14:34.200 --> 14:35.600
What gang was you trying to rep?

14:35.600 --> 14:38.520
West Side, please.
Dre, Tupac, Snoop, that whole crew.

14:38.520 --> 14:40.880
Oh, here. I got you.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.280
Here you go. Like that.

14:43.280 --> 14:46.800
Oh, yeah, yeah. Good.
Maximum respect.

14:46.800 --> 14:49.680
Rekowski! Walk with me.

14:49.680 --> 14:52.800
Well, live long and prosper.

14:55.160 --> 14:56.600
What a nerd.

15:06.920 --> 15:09.800
So, your mum spoke to me.

15:11.640 --> 15:13.880
Said you have a scholarship...

15:13.880 --> 15:15.680
..to Oxford University.

15:15.680 --> 15:19.400
Yeah, sorry about that.
She does tell everyone.

15:19.400 --> 15:21.360
Must be a pretty smart doughnut.

15:21.360 --> 15:23.120
Don't you mean "smart cookie"?

15:23.120 --> 15:24.600
They both work.

15:24.600 --> 15:26.800
Yeah,
I know all about higher education.

15:26.800 --> 15:28.800
I'm gonna apply to become
a police officer,

15:28.800 --> 15:30.640
and education helps with that.

15:30.640 --> 15:32.920
So I'm actually studying
for a degree myself.

15:32.920 --> 15:34.760
Oh, really, where are you studying?

15:34.760 --> 15:36.800
Have you heard of QuickieDegree.com?

15:36.800 --> 15:39.280
Yeah, I get the ads
in my spam folder.

15:39.280 --> 15:40.720
Oh.

15:40.720 --> 15:44.200
Your mum said Oxford's threatening
to revoke your scholarship.

15:44.200 --> 15:46.560
They haven't made a final decision.

15:46.560 --> 15:49.040
Apparently, they want you to get
three As in your A-Levels

15:49.040 --> 15:52.120
and a letter of commendation
from your supervisor.

15:53.600 --> 15:55.000
Guess who that is?

15:55.000 --> 15:56.360
Is it you?

15:56.360 --> 15:58.800
As I said, you're a smart doughnut.

15:58.800 --> 16:00.480
Cookie. They both work.

16:00.480 --> 16:03.160
I'll expect you to work hard.
Show remorse.

16:03.160 --> 16:05.920
Prove that you can learn
from your mistakes. I will.

16:07.640 --> 16:09.240
And I need you.

16:09.240 --> 16:10.800
You need me?

16:10.800 --> 16:12.920
To be my eyes and ears.

16:12.920 --> 16:15.600
Keep me posted on what's being said
and done behind my back.

16:15.600 --> 16:17.480
I don't feel comfortable snitching.

16:17.480 --> 16:19.400
Oh, no, don't think of it
as snitching.

16:19.400 --> 16:21.000
Think of it as collaborating.

16:21.000 --> 16:22.240
That sounds worse.

16:22.240 --> 16:23.920
Only cps it has connotations
with the Nazis.

16:23.920 --> 16:25.240
Yeah, that might be it.

16:25.240 --> 16:29.840
Your future depends on whether
or not I write that commendation.

16:30.760 --> 16:34.600
You need my help, I need yours.
Quid pro quo.

16:36.000 --> 16:37.200
Do we have a deal?

16:38.280 --> 16:43.520
As I said, I can be a good guy
or I can be a mean bastard.

16:43.520 --> 16:44.960
Your choice.

16:51.000 --> 16:52.720
Good girl.

16:58.640 --> 17:02.120
This must be a mistake, sir.
Rani's not a thief.

17:02.120 --> 17:03.480
Tell him your news. Go on.

17:03.480 --> 17:05.520
Mum, he doesn't care. Tell him.

17:05.520 --> 17:08.400
I got accepted
into Oxford University.

17:08.400 --> 17:11.240
With a full scholarship.
Why do you always leave that out?

17:11.240 --> 17:14.680
So, you see, sir, my daughter
is a genius, not a thief.

17:20.480 --> 17:21.840
What is going on?

17:23.920 --> 17:27.520
Is this the first time you've taken
something without paying, Rani?

17:27.520 --> 17:29.080
Yes.

17:44.680 --> 17:46.480
How many of these
do you want to watch?

17:47.480 --> 17:48.920
How many are there?

18:05.800 --> 18:09.280
All the hard work you've done
just thrown away. For what?

18:09.280 --> 18:12.640
Some sequined purses and miniskirts?

18:16.360 --> 18:18.000
It's so humiliating.

18:19.000 --> 18:21.160
Jerzy, are you going
to say anything?

18:22.440 --> 18:26.920
If you lie, cheat or steal again...

18:28.960 --> 18:31.080
..there is no place for you
in this family.

18:33.280 --> 18:34.520
Jerzy, I didn't mean...

18:34.520 --> 18:35.760
You wanted me to talk, I'm talking.

18:37.560 --> 18:41.640
If you get so much as a parking
ticket from this moment on,

18:41.640 --> 18:43.160
you are dead to us.

18:44.640 --> 18:45.920
Rekowski!

18:45.920 --> 18:47.200
We have to go in now.

18:48.240 --> 18:49.320
Come on.

19:08.360 --> 19:11.440
Hey, can you take my picture
for Instagram?

19:11.440 --> 19:13.320
What did your last servant die of?

19:14.520 --> 19:15.960
I think it was just old age.

19:15.960 --> 19:17.880
You have actual servants?

19:17.880 --> 19:20.680
Daddy does, yeah, but you can't
call them servants any more.

19:20.680 --> 19:24.200
They prefer "staff".
Will you take my picture, please?

19:24.200 --> 19:26.720
Why do you want a picture
of this dump? For my followers.

19:26.720 --> 19:29.000
You have followers?
What, like Jesus?

19:29.000 --> 19:31.520
Oh, no, I'm not like Jesus.
He only had 12.

19:31.520 --> 19:33.320
I've got 1.2 million.

19:33.320 --> 19:35.960
No, look, I do understand
what you're saying.

19:35.960 --> 19:38.880
And we've been banking
with you since 1980.

19:38.880 --> 19:40.520
It's like a couple
of little hiccups,

19:40.520 --> 19:43.120
and "Thank you for 40 years
of business, now piss off."

19:43.120 --> 19:44.520
Oy! No phones.

19:44.520 --> 19:45.800
Yes, one second, please.

19:45.800 --> 19:48.040
I'm just trying to keep a roof
over my kid's heads.

19:48.040 --> 19:50.840
