28:44.240 --> 28:47.920
but is there anything that we should
know about you or your father

28:47.920 --> 28:50.320
that could bring our company
into disrepute?

28:54.240 --> 28:55.480
There is not.

28:56.760 --> 28:58.040
Meiyou.

29:00.280 --> 29:03.520
I'm sure you'd agree
that business is based on trust.

29:05.880 --> 29:08.040
Why should
we entrust our money to you?

29:10.960 --> 29:12.200
Um...

29:15.080 --> 29:17.800
Why should, why...
Yes, um...

29:19.120 --> 29:20.520
Why?

29:25.120 --> 29:27.040
You, uh,

29:27.040 --> 29:29.000
you keep your family close.

29:29.000 --> 29:31.720
Maybe one day when you retire,
your daughter there

29:31.720 --> 29:33.480
will take the company reins,

29:33.480 --> 29:35.760
if she can stay off
her phone long enough.

29:41.480 --> 29:45.960
My, uh, my father built
this company from nothing.

29:45.960 --> 29:47.760
Worked every hour God gave.

29:47.760 --> 29:50.920
Never, never bellyached,
never asked for a...a hand-out...

29:52.120 --> 29:56.280
On the day he retired,
he had four bidders begging to buy.

29:56.280 --> 29:57.720
But he didn't sell.

29:59.200 --> 30:01.800
He handed the business to me.

30:01.800 --> 30:05.160
And, uh, I asked him,
I said, uh, you know, why?

30:05.160 --> 30:06.480
Why me?

30:06.480 --> 30:08.960
And, um, he told me, he said,

30:08.960 --> 30:12.080
"Trust, son,
is the key to any relationship,

30:12.080 --> 30:13.960
"business or otherwise.

30:13.960 --> 30:18.320
"And who can you trust
if you can't trust family?"

30:18.320 --> 30:21.680
This is a family business,
Chairman Yang.

30:21.680 --> 30:25.640
You place your trust in me,
and you become part of that family.

30:25.640 --> 30:29.200
And, sir,
I never let my family down.

30:40.720 --> 30:42.120
Mr Halloran,

30:42.120 --> 30:44.200
if you prepare the contracts
for review,

30:44.200 --> 30:45.720
we'd like to sign tomorrow.

30:47.640 --> 30:50.800
That's, uh, that's great.
That's great.

30:52.600 --> 30:55.640
Right, well,
I don't know about you, but, uh,

30:55.640 --> 30:59.720
I always find closing deals
very, very thirsty work.

30:59.720 --> 31:02.080
So, uh, please,
grab...grab a glass and, uh...

31:05.760 --> 31:06.800
Yeah.

31:14.880 --> 31:16.200
I met a girl today.

31:16.200 --> 31:17.680
Player.

31:17.680 --> 31:19.440
I want you to talk
to her about school.

31:25.560 --> 31:27.080
I know you're mad at me.

31:28.280 --> 31:30.840
But why have you got to hang out
with them when I told you not to?

31:33.520 --> 31:37.080
This is our family. Yeah?
You and me.

31:37.080 --> 31:38.680
Not them.

31:38.680 --> 31:41.040
You're not my family. You're a joke.

31:41.040 --> 31:43.760
I'm your brother. Show some respect.

31:43.760 --> 31:45.000
Respect what?

31:45.000 --> 31:47.200
They're down there getting
in a Range Rover.

31:47.200 --> 31:50.160
You're up here, unpeggin'
your little sister's underwear.

31:55.320 --> 31:57.200
What were
the other people like?

31:58.320 --> 31:59.560
Fine.

32:01.240 --> 32:03.440
Did you do everything you were told?

32:05.120 --> 32:06.280
Yeah.

32:10.040 --> 32:12.400
Is this our fault?

32:12.400 --> 32:14.000
Did we do something?

32:14.000 --> 32:15.200
No.

32:18.960 --> 32:22.840
We were too soft on you.
We should've set more boundaries.

32:22.840 --> 32:26.040
We should never have taken
the parental control off Netflix.

32:26.040 --> 32:27.560
Mum...

32:27.560 --> 32:30.680
Mum, it's not your fault.

32:33.440 --> 32:36.360
You promise me,
whatever this was about,

32:36.360 --> 32:38.160
this is the end of it.

32:40.440 --> 32:41.960
Promise.

32:52.200 --> 32:53.440
Margie.

32:53.440 --> 32:55.400
Put it down. I'd like to help.

32:56.440 --> 32:58.160
I don't need your help.
Put that down.

32:58.160 --> 33:00.120
Put it down.

33:02.960 --> 33:06.760
While I was inside, I had time
to think about all the people

33:06.760 --> 33:08.680
I effed around in my day.

33:08.680 --> 33:10.720
You're top of the list, Margie.

33:12.240 --> 33:13.480
I want to make that right.

33:13.480 --> 33:15.120
Oh, yeah?

33:15.120 --> 33:16.160
On my life.

33:16.160 --> 33:18.480
Don't promise on your life.
Don't you dare.

33:18.480 --> 33:20.880
You have fooled me 10,000 times,
not again.

33:20.880 --> 33:23.280
I said that you could stay
until the tag comes off.

33:23.280 --> 33:26.240
After that I don't want you in my
or my kids' lives a second longer.

33:26.240 --> 33:27.880
Is that clear?

33:29.880 --> 33:30.960
Crystal.

33:50.040 --> 33:53.960
Keep it down.
Fucking human pipe cleaner.

33:53.960 --> 33:55.880
Sorry.

33:55.880 --> 33:57.320
You OK?

33:57.320 --> 33:59.080
Chinese wine.

33:59.080 --> 34:02.400
Hoo! I told you. Lethal. Yeah.

34:02.400 --> 34:06.280
Oh, Diane, I raised my voice
to you the other day.

34:06.280 --> 34:09.680
That was completely unacceptable.
And I-I would like to apologise.

34:09.680 --> 34:10.800
Accepted.

34:10.800 --> 34:13.640
Yeah, in other news, I've got to be
somewhere by four today

34:13.640 --> 34:15.400
to close a very important
business deal.

34:15.400 --> 34:18.440
I was just wondering if you could
let me go just a little bit early.

34:18.440 --> 34:20.160
We finish at 3.30.

34:20.160 --> 34:22.600
I'm hoping you could make
an exception for me today, OK?

34:22.600 --> 34:24.760
Because I...I cannot be late
for this.

34:24.760 --> 34:28.280
Being late is a serious offence
in Chinese business.

34:29.440 --> 34:30.840
So...

34:30.840 --> 34:33.000
Everyone finishes at 3.30!

34:33.000 --> 34:35.240
Ah, you... For Christ's sake, woman!

34:35.240 --> 34:37.480
I'm just trying to keep
my business from going under,

34:37.480 --> 34:39.960
but no, let's...let's sweep
some old CDs.

34:43.800 --> 34:48.360
So...what's your first impressions
of our little gang?

34:51.600 --> 34:53.200
Everyone's a type.

34:53.200 --> 34:54.720
A type?

34:54.720 --> 34:58.760
Um, you've got
your right-wing blowhard,

34:58.760 --> 35:00.640
left-wing militant,

35:00.640 --> 35:02.680
celebutante,

35:02.680 --> 35:05.040
shifty old-timer,

35:05.040 --> 35:06.840
and whatever the hell he is.

35:07.880 --> 35:10.880
OK. What type am I?

35:10.880 --> 35:13.120
The bad boy.

35:13.120 --> 35:14.440
Why?

35:14.440 --> 35:16.800
What, is it
cos I've got all these tats?

35:16.800 --> 35:18.840
Yeah, tattoos aren't
that rebellious any more.

35:18.840 --> 35:20.360
You know who has tattoos?

35:20.360 --> 35:21.640
Dame Judi Dench.

35:21.640 --> 35:24.480
Well, then, Dame Judi Dench
is a straight up OG like me.

35:26.680 --> 35:27.880
What type are you?

35:29.360 --> 35:30.920
Studious Asian good girl.

35:30.920 --> 35:34.640
Mm. So, why does
the studious Asian good girl

35:34.640 --> 35:36.840
shoplift?

35:36.840 --> 35:39.240
Probably because my dad never gave me

35:39.240 --> 35:42.200
the freedom to go to parties or hang
out in a bus shelter with friends.

35:42.200 --> 35:44.760
Yeah, I've done that.
It's not as incredible as it sounds.

35:44.760 --> 35:48.880
To be fair to my dad, he grew
up in Poland under communism.

35:48.880 --> 35:52.280
So, his idea of freedom
is drinking a can of Pepsi.

35:55.680 --> 35:57.080
Would you do me a favour?

35:57.080 --> 35:58.600
What kind of favour?

35:58.600 --> 36:00.520
My sister's clever, like you.

36:00.520 --> 36:04.360
Well, she's got her GCSEs soon,
and I just can't make her study.

36:05.920 --> 36:08.240
Would you chat to her?

36:09.400 --> 36:11.440
I mean, I'm not sure what I'd say.

36:12.920 --> 36:14.440
But if you think it would help...

36:14.440 --> 36:15.960
Yeah. OK.

36:15.960 --> 36:18.320
Thank you. I really appreciate it.

36:37.280 --> 36:38.440
You OK?

36:40.240 --> 36:42.680
Yeah, um, uh, just gimme a second.

36:48.160 --> 36:51.200
I just found a deceased animal,
and I can't tell if it's over 10k.

36:51.200 --> 36:53.040
What we talking?
We're talking a dead badger.

36:53.040 --> 36:55.000
You'd better show me.
Roger that.

36:55.000 --> 36:56.440
Or should it be "bodger that"?

36:56.440 --> 36:58.000
What? Bodger and badger?

37:15.760 --> 37:17.640
What's my sister doing here?

37:17.640 --> 37:20.360
