37:56.920 --> 37:59.040
They're sat in a trap house
in Lawrence Hill.

37:59.040 --> 38:02.080
They've got a line with fiends
callin' from Bristol to Penzance.

38:02.080 --> 38:03.480
I need that phone.

38:03.480 --> 38:05.840
Oh, cos they're just gonna hand
over the line because I ask nicely?

38:05.840 --> 38:08.840
Nah. That's why you need this.

38:10.360 --> 38:11.720
Put that away.

38:11.720 --> 38:14.600
Shut up, man. Don't act like you
ain't never seen a strap before.

38:16.160 --> 38:18.560
Where's the spot?

38:18.560 --> 38:20.480
32 Rossmore Avenue.

38:21.520 --> 38:25.640
Look, if I do this for you,
Esme don't hang with you no more.

38:25.640 --> 38:28.040
And I ain't asking you,
I'm telling you.

38:54.200 --> 38:55.840
Yeah, we'll call in the council.

39:09.680 --> 39:13.960
Hi, Clive, it's Diane. Yeah, another
code blue. Fire up the incinerator.

39:13.960 --> 39:15.680
We're talking dead badger.

39:21.000 --> 39:24.480
All right, roger that.
Or should that be "bodger that"?

39:25.680 --> 39:27.480
I know, yeah.
I just thought of it now.

39:28.520 --> 39:30.240
All right, thanks, Clive, bye-bye.

39:30.240 --> 39:31.480
You stole my joke.

39:31.480 --> 39:33.880
Do you want five more hours?! No.

39:35.760 --> 39:38.520
Home time. Tools away.

39:42.360 --> 39:43.960
Great. Yeah.

39:47.080 --> 39:49.920
All right, come on,
let's pick up the pace, people.

39:49.920 --> 39:52.520
Oy! You don't give the orders.

39:52.520 --> 39:54.960
OK, come on,
let's pick up the pace, people!

39:57.440 --> 39:59.040
Everyone, freeze!

40:01.600 --> 40:03.600
Someone better explain...

40:04.640 --> 40:06.240
..about the gun.

40:10.200 --> 40:12.600
A heat gun is missing.

40:12.600 --> 40:14.520
Empty your pockets.

40:14.520 --> 40:15.920
Open your bags.

40:15.920 --> 40:17.200
I'm conducting a search.

40:18.160 --> 40:19.440
Open your bag.

40:22.160 --> 40:25.800
Files, headphones...

40:25.800 --> 40:29.120
She Gone - Coping With Divorce.

40:29.120 --> 40:32.080
Oh, I'm so sorry.
I just broke up with someone, too.

40:32.080 --> 40:33.120
How long has it been?

40:33.120 --> 40:34.840
Since Pancake Day last year.

40:34.840 --> 40:38.400
She sent me out to get a Jif lemon,
and when I came back, she was gone.

40:39.560 --> 40:42.560
People, let's not get side-tracked
by Greg's failed marriage.

40:42.560 --> 40:45.320
A heat gun is missing.
This is serious.

40:45.320 --> 40:47.680
I'll buy you a new one. OK?
Can we please just go?

41:05.560 --> 41:07.640
Is that yours too?

41:07.640 --> 41:09.280
- That one's his.
- No, it ain't.

41:09.280 --> 41:10.760
What, you're a liar and a thief?

41:10.760 --> 41:13.720
Oh, his sort, must be the thief.

41:13.720 --> 41:16.440
You do know not every coloured
person is a living saint?

41:16.440 --> 41:19.720
We don't say coloured person.
We say person of colour.

41:19.720 --> 41:22.080
I'll give you £1,000
if you can tell me the difference.

41:22.080 --> 41:24.560
Why don't you just ask people
how they'd like to be described?

41:24.560 --> 41:28.280
For instance, would you like to be
known as caveman or dinosaur?

41:28.280 --> 41:29.800
Enough!

41:29.800 --> 41:31.280
Pass it here.

41:40.920 --> 41:42.240
Is this your bag?

41:42.240 --> 41:43.840
Never seen it before.

41:43.840 --> 41:45.800
That's bullocks!
I've seen him with it.

41:45.800 --> 41:47.280
So has she.

41:47.280 --> 41:48.680
Is that true?

41:50.280 --> 41:51.440
Three words.

41:51.440 --> 41:54.960
Quid pro quo. Is this his bag?

42:00.360 --> 42:01.600
Yeah.

42:03.040 --> 42:04.280
Thank you.

42:33.000 --> 42:34.640
Everyone on the bus.

42:34.640 --> 42:36.640
Hallelujah.
Thank you so much, Diane,

42:36.640 --> 42:38.520
for those five minutes
we're never getting back.

42:44.400 --> 42:46.680
Snitches get stitches.

42:46.680 --> 42:48.000
All right, leave her alone.

42:48.000 --> 42:49.920
There's a code. What's the code?

42:49.920 --> 42:51.280
No snitching!

42:51.280 --> 42:55.160
Ha! Yeah,
the noble criminal code, huh?

42:55.160 --> 42:59.000
We can rob, steal and murder,
but, uh, telling on one another,

42:59.000 --> 43:00.480
that's...that's where
we draw the line.

43:00.480 --> 43:02.880
We're supposed to stick together.

43:02.880 --> 43:04.360
There's no "we" here.

43:23.120 --> 43:24.800
Uh-bup-bup...

43:36.880 --> 43:39.760
Empty out your pockets.
Bags go through the machine.

43:39.760 --> 43:41.320
You've got to be kidding me!

43:43.360 --> 43:44.960
I need to speak to you.

43:44.960 --> 43:46.320
I've got somewhere to be.

43:46.320 --> 43:47.880
But I really need to speak to you.

43:52.920 --> 43:54.120
Rani!

43:57.320 --> 43:59.400
Oh, come on!

43:59.400 --> 44:00.800
Belt off, please.

44:04.040 --> 44:05.560
Rekowski.

44:06.760 --> 44:08.440
Go home. This is not a Youth Club.

44:08.440 --> 44:10.440
Uh, we were...we were
just talking about...

44:10.440 --> 44:13.720
I'm sure you'll see her again soon.
Go on, Valentino. Off you go.

44:16.880 --> 44:18.520
This'll surprise you,

44:18.520 --> 44:20.160
but when I was your age...

44:21.760 --> 44:23.680
..I was unpopular too.

44:23.680 --> 44:25.880
Yeah, that is a shock.

44:25.880 --> 44:27.280
I heard the talk.

44:27.280 --> 44:30.720
You'll always get grief for doing
the right thing. So, ignore 'em.

44:30.720 --> 44:32.560
They're not your friends.

44:32.560 --> 44:35.080
The only friend you have
around here is me.

44:35.080 --> 44:39.720
And you did good today, OK?
It's going in your report.

44:39.720 --> 44:41.400
Feel better?

44:44.160 --> 44:45.480
What's going on here?

44:45.480 --> 44:49.120
Oh, a heat gun has gone missing,
sir. I'm investigating.

44:49.120 --> 44:50.600
Investigating?

44:50.600 --> 44:53.120
Well, good luck with that, Columbo.

44:57.640 --> 44:59.640
Rekowski, through the machine.

45:01.960 --> 45:03.400
Excuse me.

45:05.200 --> 45:07.200
Less gawking, more walking.

45:11.040 --> 45:12.200
Anything?

45:13.680 --> 45:15.960
What are you doing? You don't
have to take your shoes off.

45:15.960 --> 45:17.440
It's not the bloody airport.

45:17.440 --> 45:19.520
Looks like an airport, doesn't it?

45:19.520 --> 45:22.000
With the metal detector and the...

45:22.000 --> 45:23.080
Well, it isn't.

45:29.520 --> 45:31.880
All right, let's go.
It looks like an airport.

45:33.880 --> 45:35.080
Whoa, whoa!

45:35.080 --> 45:37.360
Step back! Step back!
Come back through, please, sir.

45:37.360 --> 45:39.320
I need to conduct a thorough search.

45:47.360 --> 45:48.760
Is that allowed?

45:50.160 --> 45:51.800
Well, that's not mine.

45:51.800 --> 45:54.400
No, it isn't.
Property of Probation Service.

45:54.400 --> 45:55.680
Nothing gets past me.

45:55.680 --> 45:57.520
I've caught the thief, sir.
I'm not a thief.

45:57.520 --> 46:00.000
If you'll pass me Her Majesty's
bracelets, I'll cuff him.

46:00.000 --> 46:03.120
Cuff me? Right, where's the heat
gun? Is it still on your person?

46:03.120 --> 46:05.440
I'm gonna need
some rubber gloves as well!

46:05.440 --> 46:06.760
No, you're not. Walk very slowly.

46:06.760 --> 46:09.320
You're not going to need any gloves.
We're not in Guantanamo Bay.

46:09.320 --> 46:11.480
Anything could slip out en route.
Come on.

46:15.360 --> 46:16.800
Um...

46:18.280 --> 46:21.120
That, uh, boy asked if I'd read
his sister's course work.

46:21.120 --> 46:22.280
Can I tell him that's OK?

46:24.280 --> 46:25.400
OK, quickly.

46:29.360 --> 46:33.200
You tell your sister that
I am more than happy to help.

46:36.960 --> 46:38.800
Whatever they're making you do...

46:40.320 --> 46:42.680
..please don't.

46:42.680 --> 46:44.040
Rani!

46:58.960 --> 47:00.800
Come on!

47:02.360 --> 47:03.680
Come on!

47:08.440 --> 47:09.680
Hello, Dad.

47:09.680 --> 47:10.720
Did they sign?

47:10.720 --> 47:12.480
I'm just on my way. You're late?!

47:12.480 --> 47:14.080
Jesus, I knew
I should've done this myself.

47:14.080 --> 47:16.200
Do I have to hold your hand
to sign your own bloody name?!

47:16.200 --> 47:18.440
No, Dad, everything's fine.

47:18.440 --> 47:20.160
To be late is offensive
in Chinese business.

47:20.160 --> 47:21.760
Yeah, I'm... I'm aware of that.

47:21.760 --> 47:23.680
By God, if you screw this up, I...

47:23.680 --> 47:25.160
Just call me when it's done!

47:25.160 --> 47:26.440
I'm...

47:35.680 --> 47:37.840
Define metallic bonding.

47:37.840 --> 47:41.000
The electrostatic attraction
between delocalised electrons

47:41.000 --> 47:42.920
and positive metal ions.

47:42.920 --> 47:47.600
Hmm, correct.
What is the octet rule?

47:49.480 --> 47:52.720
Elements combine
in a covalent compound

47:52.720 --> 47:56.000
with eight electrons
in their outer shell.

47:56.000 --> 47:57.240
Are they bothering you?

47:57.240 --> 47:58.280
No.

47:59.400 --> 48:03.320
Hey. Hey!
Can you keep the noise down, please?

48:03.320 --> 48:04.800
My daughter is studying up here.

48:04.800 --> 48:06.480
Fuck off! Get out of here, man.

48:09.320 --> 48:11.160
They have all the privileges
in the world,

48:11.160 --> 48:12.800
and they choose to waste
their lives.

48:12.800 --> 48:16.600
Hmm! Good.
More opportunities for you.

48:16.600 --> 48:19.760
Which of these is the best conductor
of electricity?

48:19.760 --> 48:21.400
Sodium, magnesium or alu....?

48:21.400 --> 48:23.040
Aluminium.

48:23.040 --> 48:24.720
Correct. Very good.

48:45.400 --> 48:47.360
I'm so sorry I'm late.

48:47.360 --> 48:52.760
Oh, I just, uh, had a meeting
with some, uh, new suppliers.

48:52.760 --> 48:55.520
Anyway, the exciting part, huh?

48:55.520 --> 48:57.600
I think we've got
all the paperwork sorted,

48:57.600 --> 49:02.240
so now all we need
is your signatures.

49:06.720 --> 49:09.360
Is...everything OK?

49:16.640 --> 49:20.560
An eye for an eye makes
the whole world blind.

49:22.320 --> 49:23.800
Stop!

50:02.400 --> 50:04.000
I can help with that.

50:04.000 --> 50:07.480
Well, I managed without your help
during puberty,

50:07.480 --> 50:09.920
two divorces
and my mother's dementia,

50:09.920 --> 50:11.920
so I'm pretty sure
I can scrape the paint

50:11.920 --> 50:13.640
off an old door without you.

50:16.680 --> 50:18.160
What's that?

50:18.160 --> 50:21.360
Heat gun. For stripping paint.

50:21.360 --> 50:23.680
Did you steal it? No.

50:23.680 --> 50:25.040
Frank?

50:25.040 --> 50:26.400
I borrowed it.

50:32.320 --> 50:33.720
Plug it in.

51:22.120 --> 51:23.760
Bro.

51:25.400 --> 51:29.480
Come on, bro. It's me, man.

51:29.480 --> 51:31.120
Who's there?

51:31.120 --> 51:32.680
Hey, bro, I just need two Bs, bro.

51:32.680 --> 51:35.120
Eh, no man, you've got the wrong
place. No, bro. Come on, man.

51:35.120 --> 51:36.800
Please, I've got
the money on me now.

51:36.800 --> 51:38.480
I'll just get it out. Please, man...

51:38.480 --> 51:39.800
Hey, man, I said fuck off.

51:44.240 --> 51:45.760
What are you thinking, man?

51:46.920 --> 51:48.160
Sit down.

51:48.160 --> 51:51.200
You, move. Now!

51:57.800 --> 52:00.040
Where's the line? What line?

52:00.040 --> 52:01.800
Don't mess with me, man.
Where's the phone?

52:01.800 --> 52:04.280
What the fuck are you talking about?
I'm not gonna ask you again.

52:04.280 --> 52:05.680
Where the fuck is the phone?!

52:08.720 --> 52:10.080
Under the rug, man.

52:33.320 --> 52:34.480
I dare you.

52:40.120 --> 52:41.760
You don't want to do this, man.

52:41.760 --> 52:45.160
I'm telling you, bro.
You're making a mistake, man.

53:03.960 --> 53:05.880
Do you know who you're robbing,
blud?

53:12.240 --> 53:14.400
You don't want to walk out
that door with that bag, bro.

53:14.400 --> 53:16.440
I'm telling you that right now.

53:43.800 --> 53:44.880
Hey!

53:46.400 --> 53:48.440
Go, go, go! Go! Go!

54:13.200 --> 54:15.560
Hey! This way.

55:03.040 --> 55:04.600
Sweetheart.

55:06.120 --> 55:07.720
Did they sign?

55:08.760 --> 55:10.280
Of course.

55:10.280 --> 55:12.720
We're out of the woods?

55:12.720 --> 55:14.080
Absolutely.

55:14.080 --> 55:15.520
Oh, thank God!

55:15.520 --> 55:16.720
Thank God.

55:21.400 --> 55:23.400
Did you tell your dad
the good news?

55:24.320 --> 55:26.160
Yeah. I told him.

55:26.160 --> 55:29.920
Well done, sweetheart.
I am so proud of you.

55:29.920 --> 55:31.440
Thank you.

55:43.600 --> 55:47.560
♪ What will you do
What will you do?

55:47.560 --> 55:50.320
♪ Mm

55:50.320 --> 55:54.880
♪ Every fool gets a lucky chance
or two

55:57.720 --> 56:00.840
♪ I've been waitin'
for the cards to fall

56:00.840 --> 56:04.600
♪ To catch all your mistakes

56:05.600 --> 56:07.840
♪ I've been watchin' you

56:07.840 --> 56:10.200
♪ To see you break

56:11.760 --> 56:15.360
♪ Oh, oh, oh

56:20.120 --> 56:23.800
♪ Oh, oh, oh

56:27.240 --> 56:29.520
♪ I watched you grow

56:29.520 --> 56:33.920
♪ I saw you fall again and again

56:35.120 --> 56:38.640
♪ You cut your knee
You start to bleed

56:38.640 --> 56:42.120
♪ But wouldn't let the pain in

56:42.120 --> 56:45.200
♪ You let the dogs bite
at your ankles

56:45.200 --> 56:49.520
♪ Let the sunshine burn your eyes

56:49.520 --> 56:54.320
♪ But will you just walk away
this time?

56:55.920 --> 57:01.520
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh... ♪

57:02.760 --> 57:04.240
Evening, Sarge.

57:07.960 --> 57:10.080
Lucy. Hmm?

57:17.760 --> 57:19.280
This just came in? Hmm.

57:19.280 --> 57:22.280
CCTV from Lawrence Hill.

57:24.880 --> 57:30.120
♪ I'll watch you crumble into sand

57:32.600 --> 57:36.840
♪ If the right shows mercy

57:36.840 --> 57:41.960
♪ I'll use the left hand. ♪
